{{Wireless embedded system |brand=Arris |model=Spectrum210-A |fcc_date=11/09/2017 |manuf_country=Taiwan |is_manuf=No |type=set top box, cable modem |fcc_id=ACQ-SPECTRUM210 |pwr_v=12 |pwr_amp=3 |expansion_usb_num=1 |lan_ports=1 |flags=DOCSIS 3.0, HDMI out, TOSLINK/Coaxial digital audio out, Analog audio out, RF4CE, SD Card, |802dot11_protocols=bgn }}
{{FCC ST|05/07/2018|indexme.}}
Supposedly contains 2 antennas, possibly for [http://www.ti.com/wireless-connectivity/rf4ce/overview.html RF4CE]. This device does not appear to support Wi-Fi.
Test Report DTS doc says, "The Spectrum product line includes the Spectrum 210A and Spectrum 210A. Both products are video home set tops with a wideband QAM tuner capable of up to 4 tunes. Video display capability is max 1080P60. Both products have fully compliant Docsis 3.0 embedded cable modems. The Spectrum 110A is capable of pause/live TV with internal SD card. The Spectrum 210A is capable of up to 4 DVR recordings with included HDD. Both products have capsense menu keys with Bluetooth and RF4CE wireless technologies."
It probably says "210A" twice after they did a find/replace from the document for the [[Arris Spectrum110-A]]. The Spectrum210-A appears to be a bit larger than the Spectrum 110-A, likely to make room for extra internal DVR storage.
